<i>Australian Journal of Family Law</i> 102.</a></p>
<p><sup><a name="fn93" href="#fnB93">[89]</a></sup> 	Including cases where
family violence was mentioned but not further discussed, our pre-<i>Kennon</i>
sample of 220 judgments contained only 15 (possibly 16) cases where the issue of
family violence appears to have been raised. The
post-<i>Kennon</i> cohort of 40
judgments contained nine such cases. </p>
